column1: All calculations were conducted on the LiDO 3 high performance cluster of TU Dortmund University. Calculations were automatically scheduled and ran on either an Intel Xeon E5-4604v4 or an Intel Xeon E5-2640v4 CPU
Geometries were generated using Maestro 2017-2/Macromodel with the OPLS3/Water force field with mixed torsional/low-mode sampling
column2: 100 steps per RB and 1000 steps max (default parameters). These conformers were then optimized using Gaussian 16revC01 with IEF-PCM using default settings for their respective solvent (substituting diethylether for mtbe) at the B3LYP/6-311+G(d

column1: Additional stereoisomers were treated as if they were additional conformational states so that for each microstate only up to 5 conformations with the lowest PCM energies for each solvent were treated with EC-RISM/MP2/6-311+G(d
column2: p) using the PSE2 closure for water and heptane and the PSE1 closure for all other solvents [REF1] and the resulting EC-RISM energies corrected using (c1*mu_{ex}+c2*PMV_{EC-RISM}+c3) since only neutral species were considered for the calculation of the transfer free energy. All corrections except for the one for cyclohexane have a fixed parameter of c3 = 0. Additionally
column3: the correction for water has a fixed parameter c1 = 1
column4: because for cyclohexane and water these parameters were found to be of no predictive value in previous challenges [REF2].

column1: The transfer free energy of a compound was then calculated by dG_trans=G_{wat}-G_{org}
column2: where G_{m} refers to the partition function estimate of the solvent specific free energy by summing over the conformational and tautomer states [REF3]. The log P can then be calculated by log P = dG_trans/(RT*ln(10)). The log D was calculated at a pH of 8 for SAMPL8-1
column4: 5 and 6 and at a pH of 3 for all other compounds using all calculated macrostate pKa values for the compounds by applying the multiprotic log D formula [REF4].

column1: The SEM was estimated as the convergence criterion for a single EC-RISM calculation. The uncertainty was estimated as the RMSE of the log D prediction performance in the SAMPL7 set of compounds.
